cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the evaluation of machine-generated summaries, which is a common task in natural language processing. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as summarization is a key component of information retrieval systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing evaluation measures and proposes improvements, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of n-gram overlap and synonymous concepts suggests a potential connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
